msgid "Job Management"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/jobs/index.rst:10
# 5cc6886f13ab4aa49978a9c4d243df8d
msgid "Since Salt executes jobs running on many systems, Salt needs to be able to manage jobs running on many systems. As of Salt 0.9.7, the capability was added for more advanced job management."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/jobs/index.rst:15
# 41012ff9a2e04449abec5bea1180b829
msgid "The Minion proc System"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/jobs/index.rst:17
# 9bbf98bced3745a68e6e41e505aeb29f
msgid "The Salt Minions now maintain a *proc* directory in the Salt cachedir, the *proc* directory maintains files named after the executed job ID. These files contain the information about the current running jobs on the minion and allow for jobs to be looked up. This is located in the *proc* directory under the cachedir, with a default configuration it is under */var/cache/salt/proc*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/jobs/index.rst:24
# e23d2e1fbbe740f7b41bcd5c2a5c2e01
msgid "Functions in the saltutil Module"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/jobs/index.rst:26
# cb735763a34743b2937e17963fcc6039
msgid "Salt 0.9.7 introduced a few new functions to the :doc:`saltutil</ref/modules/all/salt.modules.saltutil>` module for managing jobs. These functions are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/jobs/index.rst:30
# f065eeaee792458cad2a3ca6f530bf6b
msgid "``running`` Returns the data of all running jobs that are found in the *proc* directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/jobs/index.rst:33
# d398665846bf4a60ac2268ef4b46a7c5
msgid "``find_job`` Returns specific data about a certain job based on job id."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/jobs/index.rst:36
# bf0d2e2ee43a40ccbfb91d6d6931ce78
msgid "``signal_job`` Allows for a given jid to be sent a signal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/jobs/index.rst:39
# b022dbb245e045b998690438d65b31e3
msgid "``term_job`` Sends a termination signal (SIGTERM, 15) to the process controlling the specified job."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/jobs/index.rst:43
# ad671d929f4e4eb4b9cef29fa1244671
msgid "``kill_job`` Sends a kill signal (SIGKILL, 9) to the process controlling the specified job."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/jobs/index.rst:47
# 1500ad9929a346df9e45807aa92d4a89
msgid "These functions make up the core of the back end used to manage jobs at the minion level."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/jobs/index.rst:51
# 490f44cdc5a14df0b2e2a55c59f3ce8a
msgid "The jobs Runner"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/jobs/index.rst:53
# 8e95af0dce1542c3aa9f3ed846d90643
msgid "A convenience runner front end and reporting system has been added as well. The jobs runner contains functions to make viewing data easier and cleaner."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/jobs/index.rst:56
# 1c320abf7c094513afb4c9900cda53a9
msgid "The jobs runner contains a number of functions..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/jobs/index.rst:59
# 890aa55bb7ac4e70acc8618c4cc8c245
msgid "active"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/jobs/index.rst:61
# 7d63d7a41af545f1b4af3f32cab7140d
msgid "The active function runs saltutil.running on all minions and formats the return data about all running jobs in a much more usable and compact format. The active function will also compare jobs that have returned and jobs that are still running, making it easier to see what systems have completed a job and what systems are still being waited on."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/jobs/index.rst:72
# 774cc2a54d7d4961b0056c580449b5ab
msgid "lookup_jid"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/jobs/index.rst:74
# ec30a02e217148fcb6569c41ba0efa33
msgid "When jobs are executed the return data is sent back to the master and cached. By default is is cached for 24 hours, but this can be configured via the ``keep_jobs`` option in the master configuration. Using the lookup_jid runner will display the same return data that the initial job invocation with the salt command would display."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/jobs/index.rst:85
# 7ed40c973ffe415884679c4f3bbd7060
msgid "list_jobs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/jobs/index.rst:87
# 7fcf7930bc23445796069cadaaad0a95
msgid "Before finding a historic job, it may be required to find the job id. list_jobs will parse the cached execution data and display all of the job data for jobs that have already, or partially returned."
msgstr ""

